Exidy PacBasic with CP/M Disk Support - By RCL9 - April 23, 1983
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

Sorcerer standard basic has been relocated from C000H to 8000H with disk I/O routines residing from 7A59H to 7FFFH. It requires a 48k machine with CP/M located above 9D00H. If your CP/M is any lower, youĺre out of luck. But this has only happened to one unlucky individual.

The reasons behind this move down is because my Morrow DISCUS DJ2D disk controller ROM is located in the middle of the ROMPAC memory area. Also, the Basic does not have any disk commands. Adding them to the ROMPAC could not be done easily so the next best thing was to move it and do the modifications.

All PacBasic programs that have any machine language routines that call PacBasic Rom routines must be modified so that the addresses be relocated from C000H-DFFFH to 8000H-9FFFH. All others will work exactly the same as in Rom-Pac Basic. 

Another potential problem are programs that were saved on tape starting < 01D5H. An example would be that of a small machine language program residing at 0000H and saved as part of the basic program using the monitor SA command. This small program will have to converted to data statements and poked into zero page when the program is loaded. Only basic programs starting at 01D5H can be saved on the disk. This is because CP/MĹs zero page must be intact when the disk I/O commands are used in the basic. 

Disk I/O Commands:
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

DIR"A:FILENAME.TYP"
	This prints the directory of drive X
 	- ĹA:ĺ is optional
 	- ĹFILENAME.TYPĺ is optional
	- If you change a disk in a drive between DSAVEĺs then do a ĹDIRĺ to initialize that drive.
	 - ĹDIR "B:"ĺ will print the directory of B drive

DSAVE"A:FILENAME"
	This saves a basic program with filetype ĹBASĺ on disk X
 	- ĹA:ĺ is optional

DLOAD"A:FILENAME"
	This loads a Pac-basic program of type ĹBASĺ from disk into memory.
	 - ĹA:ĺ is optional

Disk I/O Errors:
-=-=-=-=-=-=

FF Error
	File not found error
 	- Do a ĹDIRĺ to initialize the disk or check to see if the program is really on that disk.

DF Error
	Disk full error

NB Error
	Not Pac-basic filetype ĹBASĺ program

CP/M Compatibility
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

CP/M Zero Page 0000-00FF 
Basic work area 0100-01D5 
Basic text area 01D5-7A58 
PacBasic 7A59H-9B80H
CP/M 9D00H-BEFFH (48k)
Monitor BF00H-BFFFH (48k)

To return to CP/M without destroying PacBasic and whatever program you have in memory, type ĹBYEĺ then while in the monitor type ĹGO 0ĺ and the CP/M prompt should appear. If not, do a disk boot (PacBasic will still be untouched after a cold disk boot).

In CP/M you may DIR, SAVE and ERA a program. This won't destroy PacBasic. You cannot 'STAT' a program while in CP/M because it will destroy the basic program presently in memory.

To return to Basic from CP/M go to the monitor then type ĹGO 100ĺ and the basic will be warm started. To cold start the Basic, 'GO 8000'.

If any of the disk commands do not work, go to the monitor and cold start CP/M with a 'GO D000' (DISCUS DJ2D boot), return to the monitor and ĹGO 100ĺ. Now the commands will work. 
